  "prompt": "Can you travel at the speed of light?",
  "response": "According to our current understanding of physics, particularly the theory of relativity proposed by Albert Einstein, it is not possible for objects that have mass to travel at the speed of light. As an object with mass accelerates towards the speed of light, its relativistic mass increases, which would require an infinite amount of energy to reach the speed of light itself. \n\nHowever, massless particles, such as photons (particles of light), do travel at the speed of light in a vacuum. In summary, while light can travel at the speed of light, objects with mass cannot.",
